<p>
Debian Project News is in need of contributors. Putting out Debian Project
News is a lot of work for a small team, but you can help with only a
small amount of time spent each week. We need people who read some
mailing lists which we don't read and summarize threads in them.
We also need people who keep an eye on <a
href="http://www.debianhelp.org/">DebianHELP</a>, <a
href="http://www.debian.planet.org/">Debian Planet</a>, <a
href="http://www.advogato.org/">Advogato</a>
and other online resources.
If you are interested in helping, please read this page to the end 
and <a href="mailto:debian-publicity@lists.debian.org">contact us</a> in time.
</p>

<p>
More information is available in <a href="http://wiki.debian.org/">Debian's wiki</a>. The most important pages
are:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The <a href="http://wiki.debian.org/ProjectNews">start page for the Project News</a>.</li>
  <li>The <a href="http://wiki.debian.org/ProjectNews/HowToContribute">How to contribute</a>.</li>
  <li>The <a href="http://wiki.debian.org/ProjectNews/Guidelines">basic style guidelines</a> for the Project News.</li>
  <li>The documentation about the <a href="http://wiki.debian.org/ProjectNews/Workflow">workflow used to publish the Project News</a>.</li>
</ul>

